#. Tag: title
#: systemd.xml:1223
#, no-c-format
msgid "System V Compatibility"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:1224
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"systemd is compatible with System V, allowing you to still use existing "
"System V init scripts. However, there is at least one known issue where a "
"System V init script does not work with systemd out of the box: starting a "
"service as a different user via <command>su</command> or <command>sudo</"
"command> in init scripts will result in a failure of the script, producing "
"an <quote>Access denied</quote> error."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:1232
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When changing the user with <command>su</command> or <command>sudo</"
"command>, a PAM session is started. This session will be terminated after "
"the init script is finished. As a consequence, the service that has been "
"started by the init script will also be terminated. To work around this "
"error, proceed as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:1241
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create a service file wrapper with the same name as the init script plus the "
"file name extension <filename>.service</filename>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: systemd.xml:1245
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"[Unit]\n"
"Description=<replaceable>DESCRIPTION</replaceable>\n"
"After=network.target\n"
"\n"
"[Service]\n"
"User=<replaceable>USER</replaceable>\n"
"Type=forking<co xml:id=\"co.service_wrapper.type\"/>\n"
"PIDFile=<replaceable>PATH TO PID FILE</replaceable><xref linkend=\"co."
"service_wrapper.type\" xrefstyle=\"select:label nopage\"/>\n"
"ExecStart=<replaceable>PATH TO INIT SCRIPT</replaceable> start\n"
"ExecStop=<replaceable>PATH TO INIT SCRIPT</replaceable> stop\n"
"ExecStopPost=/usr/bin/rm -f <replaceable>PATH TO PID FILE</replaceable><xref "
"linkend=\"co.service_wrapper.type\" xrefstyle=\"select:label nopage\"/>\n"
"\n"
"[Install]\n"
"WantedBy=multi-user.target<co xml:id=\"co.service_wrapper.target\"/>"
msgstr ""

